import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    avg_obesity_rate = data['rate'].mean()
    state_names = data['state']
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(state_names, data['rate'])
    ax.axhline(avg_obesity_rate, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Obesity Rate: {avg_obesity_rate:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average obesity rate across all states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    us_states = gpd.read_file('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PublicaMundi/MappingAPI/master/data/geojson/us-states.json')
    us_states = us_states.merge(data, left_on='name', right_on='state')
    us_states.plot(column='rate', cmap='OrRd', legend=True, legend_kwds={'label': "Obesity Rate", 'orientation': "horizontal"})
    plt.title("Which state has the highest obesity rate?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['rate'], data['id'])
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between obesity rates and state population?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Obesity Rate')
    plt.ylabel('State Population')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize =(10, 7))
    ax.hist(data['rate'], bins = 10, color = 'blue', edgecolor = 'black')
    ax.axvline(data['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label = 'Mean')
    ax.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label = 'Median')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of obesity rates across all states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['region'] = data['state'].apply(lambda x: x[0])
    chart = data.boxplot(column='rate', by='region', figsize=(10,6))
    chart.set_xlabel('Region')
    chart.set_ylabel('Obesity Rate')
    chart.set_title('How does the obesity rate vary across different regions of the US?')
    plt.suptitle('')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
